Description: Rim and body sherd of probably Milesian pre-Fikellura pottery cup with everted lip and handle root; white slip; interior: on lip, two rosettes (and part of third); on bowl, small spiked rosette; exterior: reserved lip; on bowl, horizontal lotus flower (fired reddish) emerging from handle root and small spiked rosette.

Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 248, no. 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.867)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 149, Nau 117, pl. 25g-i)
